R Notebook

Read the General Analytics Claims File

data <- read.csv("General_Analytics_Claims.csv")

Read Second File

data2 <- read.csv("General_Analytics_Policies.csv")

Merge data and data 2 by Policy Number

merged_data <- merge(data, data2, by="policy_number")

Attach tidyverse package

Create a Claim Severity column (new variable) in the Merged Data Table

Change Date to mdy

new_date_form <- mdy(merged_data$claim_date)

Add a new column for the updated date format to the merged_data table

merged_data <- mutate(merged_data, year = new_date_form)

Claim Severity Plot 1

ggplot(data= merged_data, mapping = aes(x= new_date_form, y=claim_severity)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method = lm, se = FALSE)+ labs(title = "Claim Severity Against Time", x = "Date", y = "Claim Severity")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Claim Severity Plot 2

ggplot(data= merged_data, mapping = aes(x= new_date_form, y=claim_severity, col = construction_type)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method = lm, se = FALSE) + labs(title = "Claim Severity Against Time", x = "Date", y = "Claim Severity")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Take the average of the Severity

avg_severity <- summarise(merged_data, mean(claim_severity))
avg_severity

Claim Severity Distribution Histogram

hist(merged_data$claim_severity, main = "Claim Severity Distribution",xlab = "Severity")
abline(v = avg_severity, col = "blue", lwd = 3)

Claim Amount Distribution Histogram

hist(merged_data$claim_amount,main = "Claim Amount Distribution",xlab = "Amount")

Get the Year Alone and Create a column for it

year_alone <- year(merged_data$year)
merged_data <- mutate(merged_data, year_alone = year(merged_data$year))

Frequency of Claims

barplot(table(merged_data$year_alone))

title(main="Frequency of Claims", xlab="Year", ylab="Count")
